# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types:
#   feat     – new feature
#   fix      – bug fix
#   chore    – maintenance / tooling / deps (no prod code change)
#   docs     – documentation only
#   refactor – code restructure without behaviour change
#   test     – adding or updating tests
#   perf     – performance improvement
#   ci       – CI/CD configuration
#   misc     – anything that doesn't fit above
#
# Rules:
#   - Use imperative mood in the subject ("add", not "added")
#   - No capital first letter, no period at the end
#   - Keep subject ≤ 72 chars
#   - Add a body (blank line + text) for "why" when helpful
#
# Examples:
#   feat(auth): add session-based admin authentication
#   fix(sdk): exclude revoked tokens from snapshot response
#   chore(deps): remove deprecated @types/bcryptjs
#   test(flags): add coverage for flag CRUD routes
